{
  "stem": "1338.5",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so Serge says to me, are you crazy?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What are you guys talking about?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They are going to shoot you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, indeed, I was wrong.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was wrong, because it turned out that the Germans were getting very itchy about the fact that some of-- Buchenwald-- you know that Buchenwald, the-- the German commander of Buchenwald got an order to kill all the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he refused, just like Paris burning, you know, the same kind of event in a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, the commander of Paris refused to burn Paris.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This commander refused to burn-- to kill prisoners in Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so, as a result, all then were-- all those were sent to Theresienstadt, which at that time became a paradise.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They brought the Red Cross and they wanted to show the Jews are still alive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I missed that opportunity [LAUGHS] and I went with Serge in a most deadly, I think that probably one of the worst killings were really going on after that, when I was herded into trains and we were killed like sardines.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there were no Jews anymore left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were Frenchmen, and Poles, and Russians primarily, and some German.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they killed you in the cars at that point?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were actually parking us inside a railroad track.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That is subsequent from after I was sent to Mauthausen, which is on the way for two weeks through Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm going from Buchenwald to Leitmeritz, which is a concentration camp next to Theresienstadt, but not-- no Jews in it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there we stayed for about two weeks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then they put us on a railroad track to go to Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Theresienstadt is-- and Leitmeritz is in Sudetenland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's the north part-- northwest corner of Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
